                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.516/39: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Arnold</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-06-25T18:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 25, 1921—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 26—8:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>26. Concession signed and approved by National Assembly to René Keilhauer for the
                    establishment of last [<hi rend="italic">a</hi>] bank of emission, authorized
                    capital $10,000,000, gold guarantee for bills will be deposited in banks in the
                    United States. Cabinet has approved 60-day option to René Keilhauer for
                    $16,000,000 loan to be guaranteed by customs receipts and customhouses to be
                    controlled by two controllers, one named by bankers and other by Government, all
                    differences to be submitted to Chief Justice of the United States as
                    arbitrator.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Arnold</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
